19990329171900000_11	They discovered that the immune defenses in the two groups were quite distinct.	discov immun defens two group quit distinct
19990329171900000_12	The immune system puts up two general types of defense against invading microbes.	immun system put two gener type defens invad microb
19990329171900000_13	In one the humoral system antibodies identify and latch on to the invading bugs.	one humor system antibodi identifi latch invad bug
19990329171900000_14	In the other the cellular system defenders spot cells that the invading bugs have infected.	cellular system defend spot cell invad bug infect
19990329171900000_15	Among the surviving patients the immune defenses were stable enough to produce a good humoral response including antibodies to attack the virus as well as a good cellular response including a substantial number of killer cells (or cytotoxic T cells) and modest amounts of interferon the body s own antiviral substance.	among surviv patient immun defens stabl enough produc good humor respons includ antibodi attack viru well good cellular respons includ substanti number killer cell cytotox cell modest amount interferon bodi antivir substanc
19990329171900000_16	Thus there appeared to be a balanced attack from both humoral and cellular defenses.	thu appear balanc attack humor cellular defens
